<div class="apidocs-main px-3 py-2 page-background ">
<section >
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>
        Welcome to the Chariot API documentation. This API allows you to integrate with our services seamlessly. Below you will find details on endpoints, request/response formats, and examples.
    </p>
</section>
<section>
    <h2>Base URL</h2>
    <p class="codecontent bg-light rounded text-center"><code>https://api.chariot.com/v1</code></p>
</section>
<section>
    <h2>Authentication</h2>
    <p>
        All requests to the Chariot API require an API key. You can obtain your API key by signing up on our platform.
    </p>
</section>
<section>
    <h2>Endpoints</h2>
    <h3>1. Get Resources</h3>
    <p><strong>Endpoint:</strong> <code>GET /resources</code></p>
    <p><strong>Description:</strong> Retrieve a list of resources.</p>
    <h4>Response:</h4>
    <pre class="codecontent bg-light rounded"><code>
{
"data": [
{
    "id": "1",
    "name": "Resource 1"
},
{
    "id": "2",
    "name": "Resource 2"
}
]
}
    </code></pre>

    <h3>2. Create Resource</h3>
    <p><strong>Endpoint:</strong> <code>POST /resources</code></p>
    <p><strong>Description:</strong> Create a new resource.</p>
    <h4>Request Body:</h4>
    <pre class="codecontent bg-light rounded"><code>
{
"name": "New Resource"
}
    </code></pre>
    <h4>Response:</h4>
    <pre class="codecontent bg-light rounded"><code>
{
"id": "3",
"name": "New Resource"
}
    </code></pre>
</section>
<section>
    <h2>Examples</h2>
    <h3>Getting All Resources</h3>
    <pre class="codecontent bg-light rounded"><code>
curl -X GET https://api.chariot.com/v1/resources \
-H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY"
    </code></pre>
</section>
